SUMMARY:Student Voter Empowerment Design Contest
DESCRIPTION:League of Women Voters of Yolo County Announce\nStudent Voter Empowerment Design Contest\nOpen to all Yolo High School Students – Contest to design posters\, bumper stickers and a variety of stickers – Encouraging and Supporting Youth Voter Registration and VOTING. Cash prizes awarded\nContest Begins Feb 13 – Submission deadline March 27\, 2026\nDrop boxes at all County and City Libraries or mailed to LWVYV P.O.Box 2463\, Woodland\, CA 95776-\nFor more information and application – Contact Judy Wohlfrom – jlwohlfrom49@yahoo.com\nCo -Sponsors of the Contest:\nYolo County Library\, Woodland Public Library\, Yolo County Election Office and Yolo County Office of Education
URL:https://thedirt.online/event/student-voter-empowerment-design-contest/
LOCATION:CA
END:VEVENT
